<title>JAPAN: TSE to limit trading of Nippon Broadcasting shares.</title>
<headline>TSE to limit trading of Nippon Broadcasting shares.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-12-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Tokyo Stock Exchange (TSE) said on Monday it would restrict trading of Nippon Broadcasting System Inc shares, which were listed on the TSE's second section on Monday.</p>
<p>The shares were bid-only all day and were quoted at 7,550 yen at the end of the session.</p>
<p>The TSE said it would prohibit securities firms from buying the shares for their own positions until the initial price of the issue had been set.</p>
<p>It also said it would require buyers to pay for the shares immediately on the first day they were traded.</p>
